    <PrimAttribute name="estTargetEndTime" id="3390c9d1-401e-429a-a05d-582e09de4270">
        <embedded/>
        <type name="TimeStamp"/>
        <access>readonly</access>
        <text>Basic Explanation

Target Gross Rate per hour on a job sheet (crane/work point) is basically

	(total incomplete moves) / (estimated Target End Date Time - work started ) * 60
	
Full Explanation

The voyage configuration 'calculate KPI rates based on moves' determines whether the statistics use moves or lifts. Lifts meaning a twin lift is one; moves meaning that twin lift is two.

'Work Started' is a date and time that is based on the first completed job item on a jobsheet (crane). If there are no completed job items on the job sheet the Work Started date time is then based on the voyage's Ship Exchange date time; if the voyage's ship exchange date time is not set the Work Started date time is then based on the voyage's Arrival date time. If the arrival date time is not set the date and time of 'now' is used from the database server.


Actual date time is the date and time of 'now' from the database server.

Estimated Target End Date Time is when it is estimated that all the jobs on a job sheet will be finished taking into account delays, actual crane rates and how many moves/lifts are left to be done.

Total Difference In Minutes is the difference from the Work Started date time and the estimated Target End Date Time; however if the Actual date time is after the work started date time then 
Total Difference In Minutes is the difference from the Actual date time and the estimated Target End Date Time.

Target Gross Rate per hour is total incomplete moves divided by Total Difference In Minutes this is then multiplied by 60.
If voyage configuration 'calculate KPI rates based on moves' is set to false then 
Target Gross Rate per hour is total incomplete lifts divided by Total Difference In Minutes this is then multiplied by 60.

Target Gross Rate per hour is basically

	(total incomplete moves) / (estimated Target End Date Time - work started ) * 60</text>
    </PrimAttribute>
